<subSubSection id="C3196578FF95FFC45C89FE5B8AFA0E16" pageId="4" pageNumber="117" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BBC36F3FF95FFC45C89FE5B8AFA0E16" blockId="4.[166,1225,221,556]" pageId="4" pageNumber="117">D i a g n o s i s. This species can be recognized from the combination of orbital and two postpronotal seta present, frons and pleura entirely black, wing hyaline, fore coxa and basal 2/3 of fore femur yellow, with widened and flattened black palp and fore tarsomeres.</paragraph>
